This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it discusses the technical challenges of 5G networks, such as authentication handover and user privacy protection, and proposes a new approach that utilizes blockchain and software defined networking (SDN) techniques to address these challenges. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as the paper also focuses on privacy protection and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as blockchain is a distributed computing technology. Additionally, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) could also be possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the technical and societal implications of 5G networks and proposes a new approach to address these challenges.
